dict.string: Search dozens of documentation sites, via DevDocs and other sources.

tell application "System Events" to set frontAppProcess to first application process whose frontmost is true # Tell the *process* to count its windows and return its front window's name. tell frontAppProcess if (count of windows) > 0 then set window_name to name of front window end if end tell
set the clipboard to window_name
# direct return for displaying in Alfred window_name
on run argv set id to (system attribute "alfred_workflow_bundleid") tell application id "com.runningwithcrayons.Alfred" to reload workflow id return id end run

## Usage Search dozens of documentation sites, via [DevDocs](https://devdocs.io/) and other sources. - <kbd>⏎</kbd>: Open the documentation site. - <kbd>⌥</kbd><kbd>⏎</kbd>: Copy the URL of the documentation site to the clipboard.
## Extra Documentation Sites - `bio`: biome docs ([rome successor](https://biomejs.dev/blog/annoucing-biome)) - `sc`: shellcheck Wiki - `pandoc`: Pandoc User Manual - `man`: man pages at [mankier.com](https://www.mankier.com/) - `hs`: Hammerspoon reference - `ep`: espanso docs - `wt`: WezTerm docs
## Utilities - `col`: named CSS colors - `keycode`: macOS keycodes - `appid`: app-id of installed macOS apps - `win`: window information for the frontmost app - `http`: HTTP status codes - `as`: AppleScript Dictionaries of installed apps - `sound`: Preview (pre-listen, technically) macOS System Sounds - Get the Uniform Type Identifier (UTI) of a selected file via the [Universal Action](https://www.alfredapp.com/help/workflows/triggers/universal-actions/)
## Reload Caches The available documentation sites are cached. In case of a recent change to a documentation site, you can manually trigger refreshing the cache via the Alfred keyword `:docs-reload`.
